    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. those are good foundational points. one of my students is struggling though, because they feel like the arguments you just gave are a bit too \"textbook\" and don't capture the actual philosophical or legal weight people use in real debates. \n\ncould you expand on the \"rule of law\" angle? like, from a serious legal or social contract perspective, why is it considered a moral necessity to have strictly enforced borders? i want them to understand the deeper principle behind it, not just the talking points.",
